{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17474296","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17474296"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T22:19:36+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T22:19:36+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11941"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11941","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11941"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.33,0.45,0.06,0.05,0.11]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4537"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"52096"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4537","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4537"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11941"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"37414"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1254"},{"type":"tags","id":"1694"},{"type":"tags","id":"4954"},{"type":"tags","id":"4959"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11638"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"6731"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8021"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8258"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15042"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16147"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44111"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44953"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"52096","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/52096"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA four-year-old girl presents to the General Practice clinic with her mother. She has a two-day history of severe sore throat, high fever, and cervical lymphadenopathy. Her mother reports this is the fourth episode the child has had over the last two years. However, it is unclear whether previous episodes were associated with high fevers, cervical lymphadenopathy, or positive serology, as medical assessment was not always sought. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, she appears unwell. Her pulse rate is 110/min, blood pressure 100/60 mmHg, respiratory rate 24/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 38.5\u00b0C. Oropharyngeal examination reveals enlarged, erythematous tonsils with exudates. Tender cervical lymph nodes are palpable bilaterally.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate plan of management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Elective tonsillectomy as soon as possible","12-month observation period for any further episodes","Reassurance that no further action is needed","Prophylactic antibiotics to prevent future episodes","Antibiotics for any subsequent infection"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis case presents a child with recurrent tonsillitis, requiring consideration of long-term management strategies. The Paradise criteria are used to guide eligibility for tonsillectomy in children suffering from recurrent tonsillitis infections. These criteria are based on the frequency and severity of tonsillitis episodes over a period of 1-3 years.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAccording to the Paradise criteria, a child is eligible for tonsillectomy if they experience:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E7 or more episodes of tonsillitis in 1 year, or\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E5 or more episodes in each of 2 consecutive years, or\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E3 or more episodes in each of 3 consecutive years\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEach qualifying episode should include a sore throat plus at least one of the following:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003ETemperature \u003E38.3\u00b0C\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ECervical lymphadenopathy (tender lymph nodes or lymph nodes \u003E2cm)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ETonsillar exudate\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EPositive culture for Group A Streptococcus\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn this case, the child has had four episodes over two years, which does not meet the Paradise criteria for \u003Cstrong\u003Eelective tonsillectomy\u003C/strong\u003E. Moreover, there is insufficient documentation of the severity of previous episodes. Therefore, the most appropriate management plan is a \u003Cstrong\u003E12-month observation period\u003C/strong\u003E to monitor for any further episodes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESimply providing \u003Cstrong\u003Ereassurance that no further action is needed\u003C/strong\u003E would be inadequate, given the recurrent nature of the child\u0027s tonsillitis. The family should be educated about the importance of seeking medical assessment for each episode to ensure proper documentation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere is no evidence to support the use of \u003Cstrong\u003Eprophylactic antibiotics\u003C/strong\u003E to prevent future episodes of tonsillitis. This approach could lead to antibiotic resistance and other adverse effects.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile \u003Cstrong\u003Eantibiotics for subsequent infections\u003C/strong\u003E may be appropriate, this decision should be made by the treating clinician at the time of each episode, based on the clinical presentation and local guidelines.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe key to managing this case is careful documentation of future episodes, including frequency, severity, and associated symptoms. This information will guide decision-making regarding the need for tonsillectomy in the future. The family should be advised to seek medical attention for each episode of suspected tonsillitis to ensure accurate records are maintained.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The Paradise Criteria guide eligibility for tonsillectomy based on frequency of tonsillitis episodes over 1-3 years.","Comprehensive documentation of tonsillitis episodes, including fever, cervical lymphadenopathy, and positive serology, is crucial for treatment decisions."],"references":["\u0160umilo D, Nichols L, Ryan R, Marshall T. Incidence of indications for tonsillectomy and frequency of evidence-based surgery: a 12-year retrospective cohort study of primary care electronic records. British Journal of General Practice. 2018;69(678):e33-e41.","Baugh, R. F., Archer, S. M., Mitchell, R. B., Rosenfeld, R. M., Amin, R., Burns, J. J., Darrow, D. H., Giordano, T., Litman, R. S., Li, K. K., Mannix, M. E., Schwartz, R. H., Setzen, G., Wald, E. R., Wall, E., Sandberg, G., \u0026amp; Patel, M. M. (2011). Clinical practice guideline: Tonsillectomy in children. Otolaryngology\u2013Head and Neck Surgery, 144(S1). https://doi.org/10.1177/0194599810389949","Randel A. AAO\u2013HNS Guidelines for Tonsillectomy in Children   and Adolescents. https://www.aafp.org/dam/brand/aafp/pubs/afp/issues/2011/0901/p566.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"37414"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11941"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"37414","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/37414"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-09-02T13:16:12+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-09-02T13:18:30+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4537"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"52096"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"descriptio